Budk&lt;U+00F3&gt;w is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Wi&lt;U+0144&gt;sko, within Wo&lt;U+0142&gt;&lt;U+00F3&gt;w County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. Prior to 1945 it was in Germany.
It lies approximately  west of Wi&lt;U+0144&gt;sko,  north-west of Wo&lt;U+0142&gt;&lt;U+00F3&gt;w, and  north-west of the regional capital Wroc&lt;U+0142&gt;aw.
The village has a population of 154.
